<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.forbes.com/technology/newswire/2003/02/27/rtr893155.html" target="top">Sega may be bought out by an American company</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Both Electronic Arts and Microsoft are looking into the possibility of buying all or part of the Japanese game maker. The news comes less than a month after Sega said it would be merging with pachinko game machine maker Sammy Corp. for financial stability. Neither MS nor EA has had formal talks with Sega, so no deal is in the wings; but the Asian Wall Street Journal said either company could become Sega's White Knight. Apparently MS approached at least one U.S. investment bank to look into buying Sega, while EA has been in talks with other Japanese game makers about a joint bid for the company. Both companies have a lot to gain. The sale would give MS a stronger foothold in Japan, while EA could snuff some of its competition. Despite churning out some great games in recent months, Sega reduced its '02/'03 net profit prediction by 90% earlier this month, and plans to announce a U.S. reorganization, cutting 20% of its workforce in the states. Thanks to Fat Tony for an <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://money.cnn.com/2003/02/28/technology/sega.reut/index.htm" target="top">additional link</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geek.com/news/geeknews/2003Apr/bga20030423019702.htm">Geek.com Geek News - Microsoft warms up to Sega buy-out</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's official: Sega is the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.gamepro.com/gamepro/financial/games/news/29022.shtml" target="top">belle of the ball</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Although Microsoft had already shown some interest in once console maker turned software publisher Sega, Redmond had never said anything official ... until this week. According to the Japanese media, MS has unofficially talked about a stock transfer plan with the slowing sinking Sega. MS, which already owns a minute share of the company, sees Sega as a chance to broaden the list of Xbox-exclusive titles. The unofficial interest Microsoft is showing Sega doesn't mean much in the grand scheme of things since Sega is already trying to elude Sammy's advances and woo Namco simultaneously. All of that's on top of the recent news of a possible Electronic Arts stock buyout for the suddenly popular game company. It's enough to make a gamer's head spin.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't see how Sega could come out of this ok.<br>
<br>
Microsoft would be the lesser of these two evils.  EA has a track record of canceling great game ideas in order to have these companies pump out endless sequels to popular titles.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=talithia>Talithia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 621<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 11:38:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1522.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is Sega screwed either way?</span><hr size=1> Imho, it would be disastrous if EA got a hold of Sega. That would be the end of the competing sports title lines as well as some other great games. It would be FAR better for MS to get them because you can almost be certain that MS would keep the Sega lines alive (likely all of it). Sure, they might turn it into XBox exclusives (unless they hit then you'll know they will port like everyone else), but it's better those games should continue to be developed. I don't want to see EA snuff out of some of it's competition.<br>
<br>
I am actually a huge fan of EA sports games and I have been for years, but the fact remains that I will go to any sports title that is superior. Recently, Sega hockey really showed a lot of promise as well as a couple other titles. I would hate to see that go away =(. As much as others might hate it, you really have to pull for Microsoft on this one.<br>
<br>
Tal<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taerendur>Taerendur</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.liquid2k.com/lanzajr/DGBoardsig2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 751<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 12:42:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1522.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/lanzajr/DGBoardsig2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is Sega screwed either way?</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with Talithia, Sega in the hands of EA would be a very bad thing.  Microsoft would help them keep pumping out the quality games, and Sega already has a track record of Xbox exclusive titles anyway.  The 2K sports line is my personal favorite, and I really feel this next year's lineup will blow any EA titles out of the water.  Hopefully Sega can remain independent, but if they get bought out then Microsoft would be the best home for them..... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=disturbedandpissed>DisturbedAndPissed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 2:17:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1522.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is Sega screwed either way?</span><hr size=1> Talithia wrote:<br>
&quot;Imho, it would be disastrous if EA got a hold of Sega&quot;<br>
<br>
I agree but for different reasons.<br>
<br>
A lot of great game development houses that have been absorbed by EA were systematically raped and then left for dead.<br>
<br>
Think Origin. Think Westwood.<br>
<br>
EA has single-handedly snuffed out the vast majority of long standing series that I had previously enjoyed, some for as long as 20 years (Ultima series).<br>
<br>
EA is good at putting out action oriented games... or games that don't require a huge amount of development time.<br>
<br>
Unfortunatley RPGs don't fit that criteria... but nothing stops EA from acquiring these titles and leading them to extinction.<br>
<br>
Bad... bad EA! I don't like you anymore! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=remfin>Remfin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Suffers from Hypocriteria</span><br>  Posts: 1467<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 10:21:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1522.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is Sega screwed either way?</span><hr size=1> Sega also has a trackrecord of &lt;insert_other_console_here&gt; exclusive titles.  Those would all disappear if MS bought them <p>Remfin<br>
