Terris - Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ppatty>PPatty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/sgnon/pattyscreams.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 633<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/03 7:37:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1522.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/sgnon/pattyscreams.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is Sega screwed either way?</span><hr size=1> Say what you want about Microsoft, the company has a pretty good track record for publishing games, going all the way back to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Flight Simulator</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Off the top of my head, I can't think of any MS-published games that were bad, except for maybe <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Asheron's Call</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=galamar>Galamar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/03 7:46:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1522.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://pws.chartermi.net/~aakoch/images/Face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is Sega screwed either way?</span><hr size=1> You mean Bill Gates isn't the great Satan and instead might just be a decent and very, very good businessman?<br>
<br>
The mind reels. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I think Namco would be a pretty decent patron for Sony, but MS has a lot more capital to throw around and having Sega would give them some history and background in the console market.  Good for MS and Namco, down with EA taking them over. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=412636" target="top">Galamar Goldleaf</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
